==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mara
<hw>Ma"ra</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>mara</ets> nightmare,
an ogress. See <er>Nightmare</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Norse Myth.)</fld>
<def>A female demon who torments people in sleep by crouching on their
chests or stomachs, or by causing terrifying visions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mara</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mara
<hw>Ma"ra</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The Patagonian
cavy, a hare-like rodent (<spn>Dolichotis patagonum</spn> or
<spn>Dolichotis Patagonicus</spn>) of the pampas of Argentina.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marabou</ent>⟦br⟧
